{
  "doc_id": "1573",
  "text": "Recent studies indicate that physically attractive politicians generally obtain more votes [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . This research note extended this literature by arguing that physical attractiveness might well benefit politicians not just on, but also after Election Day. Using data on German MPs' extra-parliamentary positions, we indeed illustrate that (perceived) likability benefits (especially female) MPs for both private-and public-sector jobs. The likability effects thus uncovered are both statistically and substantively meaningful. For MPs' perceived physical attractiveness, we find that it may well have an indirect effect on politicians' extra-parliamentary activities, but a direct effect of beauty cannot be substantiated.",
